tp://www.riaj.or.jp/issue/record/1997/199710.pdf |title=RIAJ > The Record > October 1997 > Certified Awards (August 1997) |work=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=2 August 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018041846/http://www.riaj.or.jp/issue/record/1997/199710.pdf |archivedate=18 October 2014 |df= }}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Netherlands|award=Gold|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=Morning Glory|accessdate=13 September 2012|certyear=1996|relmonth=10|relyear=1995}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|award=Platinum|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=(What's The Story) Morning...|accessdate=25 July 2017|recent=website|id=3707}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Norway|award=Platinum|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=Morning Glory|accessdate=9 June 2012|certyear=1997|relmonth=10|relyear=1995}}\n{{certification Table Entry|artist=Oasis|title=(What's the Story) Morning Glory?|type=album|relyear=1995|certyear=1996|region=Spain|award=Platinum|number=2|certref=<ref name=\"Spanish certifications 1995\u20131999\">{{cite book|url=http://www.mediafire.com/view/pd758fesp2w7i7f|title=Solo Exitos 1959\u20132002 Ano A Ano: Certificados > 1995\u20131999|publisher=Iberautor Promociones Culturales|isbn=978-84-8048-639-2|year=2005}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Sweden|award=Platinum|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=(What's the Story) Morning Glory?|accessdate=9 June 2012|certyear=1996|relmonth=10|relyear=1995}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Switzerland|award=Gold|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=(What's The Story) Morning...|accessdate=9 June 2012|relyear=1995}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Thailand|award=Gold|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=(What's the Story) Morning Glory?|relyear=1996|salesamount=10,000^|certref=<ref name=\"oasis\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|award=Platinum|number=15|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=(What's the Story) Morning Glory?|accessdate=9 June 2012|salesamount=4,700,000|salesref=<ref name=\"UK sales\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|award=Platinum|number=4|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=(What's the Story) Morning Glory?|accessdate=9 June 2012}}\n{{Certification Table Summary}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Europe|award=Platinum|number=6|type=album|artist=Oasis|title=(What's the Story) Morning Glory?|accessdate=9 June 2012|certyear=1997}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of best-selling albums in the United Kingdom]]\n* [[List of best-selling albums]]\n* [[List of best-selling albums in the United Kingdom#Top best-selling albums by UK Chart|Top best-selling albums by UK Chart]]\n\n==References==\n'''Footnotes'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n'''Bibliography'''\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|year=2000|title=Christgau's Consumer Guide: Albums of the '90s|publisher=Macmillan|isbn=978-0-312-24560-3|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/christgausconsum00chri_0}}\n* Harris, John. ''Britpop!: Cool Britannia and the Spectacular Demise of English Rock''. Da Capo Press, 2004. {{ISBN|0-306-81367-X}}\n* Bennet, Andy; Stratton, John. ''Britpop and the English Music Tradition''. Ashgate, 2010. {{ISBN|978-0-7546-6805-3}}\n* ''[[Seven Ages of Rock]]: What the World is Waiting For''. BBC, 2007.\n* {{cite book|ref={{SfnRef|Sheffield|2004}}|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|authorlink=Rob Sheffield|chapter=Oasis|editor1-first=Nathan|editor1-last=Brackett|editor1-link=Nathan Brackett|editor2-first=Christian|editor2-last=Hoard|title=The New Rolling Stone Album Guide|publisher=Simon & Schuster|edition=4th|year=2004|isbn=978-0-7432-0169-8|title-link=The Rolling Stone Album Guide}}\n\n{{Oasis}}\n{{Brit British Album}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Whats The Story Morning Glory?}}\n[[Category:1995 albums]]\n[[Category:Creation Records albums]]\n[[Category:Epic Records albums]]\n[[Category:Oasis (band) albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Owen Morris]]\n[[Category:Albums involved in plagiarism controversies]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Rockfield Studios]]\n[[Category:Brit Award for British Album of the Year]]\n", "name_user": "Zmbro", "label": "safe", "comment": "updated perTemplate:Infobox_song#Parameters", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/(What%27s_the_Story)_Morning_Glory%3F"}
{"title_page": "Ring Fit Adventure", "text_new": "{{Infobox video game\n| collapsible = \n| state = \n| italic title = \n| title = Ring Fit Adventure\n| image = Ringfitadventure.jpg\n| alt = \n| caption = Icon art, depicting the playable character, enemies and the Ring-Con accessory\n| developer = [[Nintendo EPD]]{{efn|Graphic Assistance by [[1-UP Studio]]}}\n| publisher = [[Nintendo]]\n| director = Hiroshi Matsunaga\n| producer = Kouichi Kawamoto\n| designer = {{ubl|Naoya Yamamoto|Ryosuke Suzuki}}\n| composer = {{ubl|Shinji Ushiroda|Maasa Miyoshi|Shiho Fujii|Asuka Hayazaki}}\n| programmer = Shinji Okane\n| artist = Takafumi Kiuchi\n| series = \n| engine = \n| platforms = [[Nintendo Switch]]\n| released = October 18, 2019\n| genre = [[Exergaming|Exergame]], [[Role-playing video game|role-playing]]\n| modes = [[Single-player]]\n| writer = {{ubl|Mari Shirakawa|Yuichiro Ito}}\n}}\n\n'''''Ring Fit Adventure''''' is an [[Exergaming|exercising]] [[Action role-playing game|action-RPG]] developed and published by [[Nintendo]] for the [[Nintendo Switch]]. The game comes with two physical components: the Ring-Con, a flexible, hard-plastic ring that the user holds and one [[Joy-Con]] slots into, and a Leg Strap, a piece of fabric affixed to the user's leg that holds the other Joy-Con.\n\nThe game's main mode has the player complete a [[turn-based role-playing game]], where player movements and battle actions are based on performing certain physical activities using the Ring-Con and Leg Strap, with the [[motion control]]s within the [[Joy-Con]] sensing the player's movement. Other modes include general guided fitness routines and party-style games. These activities are centered around common fitness [[exercise]]s, making the game part of Nintendo's \"quality of life\" goals in line with a similar game of theirs, ''[[Wii Fit]]''. The game was released worldwide on October 18, 2019. As of December 2019, the game has sold over 2 million copies worldwide, making it one of the [[List of best-selling Nintendo Switch video games|best-selling games]] on the system.\n\n==Gameplay==\n[[File:Ring_Fit_Adventure_Screenshot.jpg|left|thumb|Combat in ''Ring Fit Adventure'' has the player complete an exercise move (shown on left) to defeat enemies in game.]]\n''Ring Fit Adventure'' ships with the Ring-Con and Leg Strap, which have docks to hold the Switch's Joy-Con. These accessories are required to play the game, as the player's interactions with them are tracked by the [[motion control]]s built into the Joy-Con.<ref name=\"verge announce\">{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2019/9/12/20860767/ring-fit-adventure-nintendo-switch-fitness-game-price-release-date | title = Nintendo\u2019s Ring Fit Adventure is Wii Fit meets Final Fantasy on the Switch | first = Andrew | last= Webster | date = September 12, 2019 | accessdate = September 12, 2019 | work = [[The Verge]] }}</ref>\n\nThe game's main mode is a role-playing game, in which the player takes the role of a young athlete that meets a sentient Ring, and they team up to take down an evil, bodybuilding dragon named Dragaux. The player moves their character across the game's overworld and into various dungeons, where they encounter monsters to fight. Moving across the game world is similar to a [[rail shooter]]; the player moves along a fixed path by running in place, jumps over obstacles by squeezing and releasing the Ring-Con, and can fire projectiles at items by squeezing in the Ring-Con in the target direction. When the player encounters monsters, the game uses turn-based combat as in most role-playing games. The player attacks the enemies by performing one of about thirty different exercises, with the amount of damage they deal based on how effectively they completed the exercise. When the monsters attack, the player can defend by pressing and holding the Ring-Con into their abdomen for as long as possible during the attack. Defeating monsters earns the player-character [[experience point]]s, and as they level up, they can unlock additional exercises with more potent damage. Exercises are classified by color, each color corresponding to a general part of the body the exercise is geared towards, like shoulders or [[Aerobic exercise|cardio]]; monsters are also marked by colors, and exercises of the same color are more effective against them.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/>\n\nIn addition to the adventure mode, the game includes a general fitness routine mode that allows one to perform the exercises, assisted by the game, but without the gamification elements. The game also has several [[mini-game]]s based on certain exercises, which can be used by a single player to challenge themselves or can be used with multiple players each taking a turn to beat the others.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/> An update in late March of 2020 also added a \"Rhythm Mode\", which allows the user to move along to soundtrack from the game. This mode also includes some music from other Nintendo games such as ''Jump up superstar ''From''[[Super Mario Odyssey]]'', ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild]]'', ''[[Splatoon 2]]'', and ''[[Wii Fit]]''. \n\nThe game includes the option to enable only quiet exercises to avoid disturbing others nearby. For example, in quiet mode, the running-in-place in the adventure mode is replaced by performing squats.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/>\n\n==Development==\nThe game was first teased in early September 2019 with a video showing people using the Ring-Con and Leg Strap without showing the game,<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2019/9/5/20851907/nintendo-new-motion-control-experience-switch-fitness-joy-con-controller-tease-september-12 | title = Nintendo teases strange new motion control experience for Switch | first = Chaim | last =Gartenburg | date = September 5, 2019 | accessdate = September 5, 2019 | work = [[The Verge]] }}</ref> with a full announcement of the game a week later.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/>\n\nSeveral journalists observed that the game fits into Nintendo's long-running \"[[quality of life]]\" program, to introduce more physical activity into the playing of video games, that had been started by [[Satoru Iwata]] with the introduction of the [[Wii]] console, particularly in the game ''[[Wii Fit]]''.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/nintendo-switch/2019/9/12/20862392/nintendo-switch-ring-controller-ring-fit-adventure-release-dates-exergaming | title=  Nintendo Switch\u2019s new ring controller game is Ring Fit Adventure | first=  Owen S. |last= Good | date = September 12, 2019 | accessdate = September 12, 2019 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/nintendo-switchs-weird-new-fitness-device-detailed/1100-6469798/|title=Nintendo Switch's Weird New Fitness Device Detailed: Ring Fit Adventure Releases Soon|website=GameSpot|accessdate=September 12, 2019|date=September 12, 2019|first=Oscar|last=Dayus}}</ref> Parts of the design of the Nintendo Switch had been from player feedback from ''Wii Fit'' looking to make the controllers smaller so they could be strapped to the body and used in more possible ways.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/314530/The_Nintendo_Switch_JoyCons_and_even_Labo_are_the_result_of_Wiiera_feedback.php | title = The Nintendo Switch, Joy-Cons, and even Labo are the result of Wii-era feedback | first = Alissa | last= McAloon | date = February 9, 2018 | accessdate = February 9, 2018 | website = [[Gamasutra]] }}</ref>\n\n''Ring Fit Adventure'' was released in North America on October 18, 2019. The game, shipping with the Ring-Con and Leg Strap, cost slightly higher than a typical game, at an [[MSRP]] of {{USD|79.99}} compared to the typical {{USD|59.99}}.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/>\n\nOn March 26, 2020 a free update was released, adding a [[rhythm game]] mode.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McWhertor |first1=Michael |title=Ring Fit Adventure adds a rhythm game mode with music from Splatoon 2, Breath of the Wild |url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/3/26/21195328/ring-fit-adventure-rhythm-game-mode-update-music |website=Polygon |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=en |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Expand section|date=October 2019}}\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = 83/100<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/ring-fit-adventure |title=Ring Fit Adventure for Switch Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| GRadar = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Loveridge |first=Sam |date=October 18, 2019 |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/ring-fit-adventure-review/|title=Ring Fit Adventure Review |website=[[GamesRadar+]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| IGN = 7.8/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Dornbush |first=Jonathon |date=October 17, 2019 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/10/17/ring-fit-adventure-for-nintendo-switch-review |title=Ring Fit Adventure for Nintendo Switch Review |website=[[IGN]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| JXV = 16/20<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jeuxvideo.com/test/1127829/ring-fit-adventure-quand-sport-et-jeu-video-ne-font-plus-qu-un.htm |title=Test: Ring Fit Adventure: When sport and video games become one |website=[[Jeuxvideo.com]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| NLife = 8/10<ref name=\"nlife_review\">{{cite web |last=Scullion |first=Chris |date=October 22, 2019 |url=https://www.nintendolife.com/reviews/nintendo-switch/ring_fit_adventure|title=Ring Fit Adventure Review |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Ring Fit Adventure'' received \"generally favorable\" reviews, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]], with a score of 83/100. Many critics agree that while Ring Fit Adventure is not designed for strength training, it is effective exercise for maintaining fitness. The RPG elements of the game are very simplistic; which allows casual videogame-players to play the game with ease, but which can be disappointing for fans of RPGs who want more of a strategic challenge.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/ring-fit-adventure |title=The Legend of Zelda: Ring Fit Adventure for Switch Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Sales ===\n''Ring Fit Adventure'' debuted at #3 in the UK,<ref>{{cite web |last=Batchelor |first=James |date=October 21, 2019 |url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2019-10-21-uk-charts-switch-dominates-as-the-witcher-3-leads-slew-of-new-releases |title=UK Charts: Switch dominates as The Witcher 3 leads slew of new releases |website=[[Gamer Network|GamesIndustry.biz]] |accessdate=October 21, 2019}}</ref> and #1 in Japan and South Korea.<ref>https://gematsu.com/2019/10/famitsu-sales-10-14-19-10-20-19</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/detail.php?sn=187740 |title=MediaCreate 10 \u6708 14 \u65e5\uff5e10 \u6708 20 \u65e5\u4e00\u9031\u92b7\u552e\u6392\u884c\u699c \u300a\u5065\u8eab\u74b0\u5927\u5192\u96aa\u300b\u518d\u6380\u9ad4\u611f\u71b1\u6f6e |website=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9 |accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref> In Japan, it sold 68,497 copies within its first week on sale, which placed it at number one on the all format sales chart.<ref>{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |date=October 23, 2019 |url=https://gematsu.com/2019/10/famitsu-sales-10-14-19-10-20-19\u00a0|title=Famitsu Sales: 10/14/19 \u2013 10/20/19 [Update] |publisher=Gematsu |accessdate=January 2, 2020}}</ref> As of December 2019, the game has shipped 2.17 million units worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2020/200130_3e.pdf|title=Million Sellers Titles of Nintendo Products|page=7|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nDue to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], demand for the game increased significantly, creating shortages.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Fears Spark a Run on Nintendo's Ring Fit Adventure |url=https://www.wired.com/story/ring-fit-shortage-coronavirus-covid-19/ |website=Wired |accessdate=13 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Chinese consumers snap up yoga mats, video games, condoms as coronavirus keeps them at home |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-consumer/chinese-consumers-snap-up-yoga-mats-video-games-condoms-as-coronavirus-keeps-them-at-home-idUSKBN20J1JL |website=Reuters |accessdate=13 March 2020 |language=en |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards ===\nThe game was nominated for \"Best Family Game\" at [[The Game Awards 2019]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Winslow |first=Jeremy |date=November 19, 2019 |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/the-game-awards-2019-nominees-full-list/1100-6471564/ |title=The Game Awards 2019 Nominees Full List |website=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref> for \"Family Game of the Year\" at the [[23rd Annual D.I.C.E. Awards]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Chalk |first=Andy |date=January 13, 2020 |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/control-and-death-stranding-get-eight-nominations-each-for-the-2020-dice-awards/ |title=Control and Death Stranding get 8 nominations each for the 2020 DICE Awards |website=[[PC Gamer]] |accessdate=January 18, 2020}}</ref> and for \"Game Beyond Entertainment\" at the [[16th British Academy Games Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Stuart |first=Keith |date=March 3, 2020 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/games/2020/mar/03/death-stranding-and-control-dominate-bafta-games-awards-nominations |title=Death Stranding and Control dominate Bafta games awards nominations |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://www.nintendo.co.uk/Games/Nintendo-Switch/Ring-Fit-Adventure-1638708.html Official website] (UK)\n*[https://ringfitadventure.nintendo.com/ Official website]\n{{Nintendo Switch}}\n\n[[Category:2019 video games]]\n[[Category:Exergames]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Entertainment Planning & Development games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch-only games]]\n[[Category:Role-playing video games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox video game\n| collapsible = \n| state = \n| italic title = \n| title = Ring Fit Adventure\n| image = Ringfitadventure.jpg\n| alt = \n| caption = Icon art, depicting the playable character, enemies and the Ring-Con accessory\n| developer = [[Nintendo EPD]]{{efn|Graphic Assistance by [[1-UP Studio]]}}\n| publisher = [[Nintendo]]\n| director = Hiroshi Matsunaga\n| producer = Kouichi Kawamoto\n| designer = {{ubl|Naoya Yamamoto|Ryosuke Suzuki}}\n| composer = {{ubl|Shinji Ushiroda|Maasa Miyoshi|Shiho Fujii|Asuka Hayazaki}}\n| programmer = Shinji Okane\n| artist = Takafumi Kiuchi\n| series = \n| engine = \n| platforms = [[Nintendo Switch]]\n| released = October 18, 2019\n| genre = [[Exergaming|Exergame]], [[Role-playing video game|role-playing]]\n| modes = [[Single-player]]\n| writer = {{ubl|Mari Shirakawa|Yuichiro Ito}}\n}}\n\n'''''Ring Fit Adventure''''' is an [[Exergaming|exercising]] [[Action role-playing game|action-RPG]] developed and published by [[Nintendo]] for the [[Nintendo Switch]]. The game comes with two physical components: the Ring-Con, a flexible, hard-plastic ring that the user holds and one [[Joy-Con]] slots into, and a Leg Strap, a piece of fabric affixed to the user's leg that holds the other Joy-Con.\n\nThe game's main mode has the player complete a [[turn-based role-playing game]], where player movements and battle actions are based on performing certain physical activities using the Ring-Con and Leg Strap, with the [[motion control]]s within the [[Joy-Con]] sensing the player's movement. Other modes include general guided fitness routines and party-style games. These activities are centered around common fitness [[exercise]]s, making the game part of Nintendo's \"quality of life\" goals in line with a similar game of theirs, ''[[Wii Fit]]''. The game was released worldwide on October 18, 2019. As of December 2019, the game has sold over 2 million copies worldwide, making it one of the [[List of best-selling Nintendo Switch video games|best-selling games]] on the system.\n\n==Gameplay==\n[[File:Ring_Fit_Adventure_Screenshot.jpg|left|thumb|Combat in ''Ring Fit Adventure'' has the player complete an exercise move (shown on left) to defeat enemies in game.]]\n''Ring Fit Adventure'' ships with the Ring-Con and Leg Strap, which have docks to hold the Switch's Joy-Con. These accessories are required to play the game, as the player's interactions with them are tracked by the [[motion control]]s built into the Joy-Con.<ref name=\"verge announce\">{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2019/9/12/20860767/ring-fit-adventure-nintendo-switch-fitness-game-price-release-date | title = Nintendo\u2019s Ring Fit Adventure is Wii Fit meets Final Fantasy on the Switch | first = Andrew | last= Webster | date = September 12, 2019 | accessdate = September 12, 2019 | work = [[The Verge]] }}</ref>\n\nThe game's main mode is a role-playing game, in which the player takes the role of a young athlete that meets a sentient Ring, and they team up to take down an evil, bodybuilding dragon named Dragaux. The player moves their character across the game's overworld and into various dungeons, where they encounter monsters to fight. Moving across the game world is similar to a [[rail shooter]]; the player moves along a fixed path by running in place, jumps over obstacles by squeezing and releasing the Ring-Con, and can fire projectiles at items by squeezing in the Ring-Con in the target direction. When the player encounters monsters, the game uses turn-based combat as in most role-playing games. The player attacks the enemies by performing one of about thirty different exercises, with the amount of damage they deal based on how effectively they completed the exercise. When the monsters attack, the player can defend by pressing and holding the Ring-Con into their abdomen for as long as possible during the attack. Defeating monsters earns the player-character [[experience point]]s, and as they level up, they can unlock additional exercises with more potent damage. Exercises are classified by color, each color corresponding to a general part of the body the exercise is geared towards, like shoulders or [[Aerobic exercise|cardio]]; monsters are also marked by colors, and exercises of the same color are more effective against them.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/>\n\nIn addition to the adventure mode, the game includes a general fitness routine mode that allows one to perform the exercises, assisted by the game, but without the gamification elements. The game also has several [[mini-game]]s based on certain exercises, which can be used by a single player to challenge themselves or can be used with multiple players each taking a turn to beat the others.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/> An update in late March of 2020 also added a \"Rhythm Mode\", which allows the user to move along to soundtrack from the game. This mode also includes some music from other Nintendo games such as ''[[Super Mario Odyssey]]'', ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild]]'', ''[[Splatoon 2]]'', and ''[[Wii Fit]]''. \n\nThe game includes the option to enable only quiet exercises to avoid disturbing others nearby. For example, in quiet mode, the running-in-place in the adventure mode is replaced by performing squats.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/>\n\n==Development==\nThe game was first teased in early September 2019 with a video showing people using the Ring-Con and Leg Strap without showing the game,<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2019/9/5/20851907/nintendo-new-motion-control-experience-switch-fitness-joy-con-controller-tease-september-12 | title = Nintendo teases strange new motion control experience for Switch | first = Chaim | last =Gartenburg | date = September 5, 2019 | accessdate = September 5, 2019 | work = [[The Verge]] }}</ref> with a full announcement of the game a week later.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/>\n\nSeveral journalists observed that the game fits into Nintendo's long-running \"[[quality of life]]\" program, to introduce more physical activity into the playing of video games, that had been started by [[Satoru Iwata]] with the introduction of the [[Wii]] console, particularly in the game ''[[Wii Fit]]''.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/nintendo-switch/2019/9/12/20862392/nintendo-switch-ring-controller-ring-fit-adventure-release-dates-exergaming | title=  Nintendo Switch\u2019s new ring controller game is Ring Fit Adventure | first=  Owen S. |last= Good | date = September 12, 2019 | accessdate = September 12, 2019 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/nintendo-switchs-weird-new-fitness-device-detailed/1100-6469798/|title=Nintendo Switch's Weird New Fitness Device Detailed: Ring Fit Adventure Releases Soon|website=GameSpot|accessdate=September 12, 2019|date=September 12, 2019|first=Oscar|last=Dayus}}</ref> Parts of the design of the Nintendo Switch had been from player feedback from ''Wii Fit'' looking to make the controllers smaller so they could be strapped to the body and used in more possible ways.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/314530/The_Nintendo_Switch_JoyCons_and_even_Labo_are_the_result_of_Wiiera_feedback.php | title = The Nintendo Switch, Joy-Cons, and even Labo are the result of Wii-era feedback | first = Alissa | last= McAloon | date = February 9, 2018 | accessdate = February 9, 2018 | website = [[Gamasutra]] }}</ref>\n\n''Ring Fit Adventure'' was released in North America on October 18, 2019. The game, shipping with the Ring-Con and Leg Strap, cost slightly higher than a typical game, at an [[MSRP]] of {{USD|79.99}} compared to the typical {{USD|59.99}}.<ref name=\"verge announce\"/>\n\nOn March 26, 2020 a free update was released, adding a [[rhythm game]] mode.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McWhertor |first1=Michael |title=Ring Fit Adventure adds a rhythm game mode with music from Splatoon 2, Breath of the Wild |url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/3/26/21195328/ring-fit-adventure-rhythm-game-mode-update-music |website=Polygon |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=en |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Expand section|date=October 2019}}\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = 83/100<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/ring-fit-adventure |title=Ring Fit Adventure for Switch Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| GRadar = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Loveridge |first=Sam |date=October 18, 2019 |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/ring-fit-adventure-review/|title=Ring Fit Adventure Review |website=[[GamesRadar+]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| IGN = 7.8/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Dornbush |first=Jonathon |date=October 17, 2019 |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/10/17/ring-fit-adventure-for-nintendo-switch-review |title=Ring Fit Adventure for Nintendo Switch Review |website=[[IGN]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| JXV = 16/20<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jeuxvideo.com/test/1127829/ring-fit-adventure-quand-sport-et-jeu-video-ne-font-plus-qu-un.htm |title=Test: Ring Fit Adventure: When sport and video games become one |website=[[Jeuxvideo.com]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| NLife = 8/10<ref name=\"nlife_review\">{{cite web |last=Scullion |first=Chris |date=October 22, 2019 |url=https://www.nintendolife.com/reviews/nintendo-switch/ring_fit_adventure|title=Ring Fit Adventure Review |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Ring Fit Adventure'' received \"generally favorable\" reviews, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]], with a score of 83/100. Many critics agree that while Ring Fit Adventure is not designed for strength training, it is effective exercise for maintaining fitness. The RPG elements of the game are very simplistic; which allows casual videogame-players to play the game with ease, but which can be disappointing for fans of RPGs who want more of a strategic challenge.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/ring-fit-adventure |title=The Legend of Zelda: Ring Fit Adventure for Switch Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Sales ===\n''Ring Fit Adventure'' debuted at #3 in the UK,<ref>{{cite web |last=Batchelor |first=James |date=October 21, 2019 |url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2019-10-21-uk-charts-switch-dominates-as-the-witcher-3-leads-slew-of-new-releases |title=UK Charts: Switch dominates as The Witcher 3 leads slew of new releases |website=[[Gamer Network|GamesIndustry.biz]] |accessdate=October 21, 2019}}</ref> and #1 in Japan and South Korea.<ref>https://gematsu.com/2019/10/famitsu-sales-10-14-19-10-20-19</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/detail.php?sn=187740 |title=MediaCreate 10 \u6708 14 \u65e5\uff5e10 \u6708 20 \u65e5\u4e00\u9031\u92b7\u552e\u6392\u884c\u699c \u300a\u5065\u8eab\u74b0\u5927\u5192\u96aa\u300b\u518d\u6380\u9ad4\u611f\u71b1\u6f6e |website=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9 |accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref> In Japan, it sold 68,497 copies within its first week on sale, which placed it at number one on the all format sales chart.<ref>{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |date=October 23, 2019 |url=https://gematsu.com/2019/10/famitsu-sales-10-14-19-10-20-19\u00a0|title=Famitsu Sales: 10/14/19 \u2013 10/20/19 [Update] |publisher=Gematsu |accessdate=January 2, 2020}}</ref> As of December 2019, the game has shipped 2.17 million units worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2020/200130_3e.pdf|title=Million Sellers Titles of Nintendo Products|page=7|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nDue to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], demand for the game increased significantly, creating shortages.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Fears Spark a Run on Nintendo's Ring Fit Adventure |url=https://www.wired.com/story/ring-fit-shortage-coronavirus-covid-19/ |website=Wired |accessdate=13 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Chinese consumers snap up yoga mats, video games, condoms as coronavirus keeps them at home |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-consumer/chinese-consumers-snap-up-yoga-mats-video-games-condoms-as-coronavirus-keeps-them-at-home-idUSKBN20J1JL |website=Reuters |accessdate=13 March 2020 |language=en |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards ===\nThe game was nominated for \"Best Family Game\" at [[The Game Awards 2019]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Winslow |first=Jeremy |date=November 19, 2019 |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/the-game-awards-2019-nominees-full-list/1100-6471564/ |title=The Game Awards 2019 Nominees Full List |website=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref> for \"Family Game of the Year\" at the [[23rd Annual D.I.C.E. Awards]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Chalk |first=Andy |date=January 13, 2020 |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/control-and-death-stranding-get-eight-nominations-each-for-the-2020-dice-awards/ |title=Control and Death Stranding get 8 nominations each for the 2020 DICE Awards |website=[[PC Gamer]] |accessdate=January 18, 2020}}</ref> and for \"Game Beyond Entertainment\" at the [[16th British Academy Games Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Stuart |first=Keith |date=March 3, 2020 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/games/2020/mar/03/death-stranding-and-control-dominate-bafta-games-awards-nominations |title=Death Stranding and Control dominate Bafta games awards nominations |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://www.nintendo.co.uk/Games/Nintendo-Switch/